text: The green spotted tree frog (Rhacophorus viridimaculatus) is a frog. It lives in Vietnam in Ha Giang Province and Tuyen Quang Province. Scientists think it might also live in China, in Guangxi Province. Scientists have seen it between 600 and 1300 meters above sea level. ==First paper== * ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Rhacophorus viridimaculatus
